{"/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_beiderbecke_ver01/data/sn83045462/00280657463/1924011801/0264.xml":{"full_text":"18\nHAYNES ANSWERS\nPINCHOT ASSAULT\nHints Butler's Post in Phila\ndelphia Sign of Failure of\nii State Heads,\nProhibition Commissioner Haynes\nhas struck back at Gov. Plnchot for\nthe latter's attack on prohibition en\nforcement before the Anti-Saloon\nleague convention.\nCriticising the Pennsylvania gov\nernor, Mr. Haynes last night de\nclared \u201cthe fact that Philadelphia\nhad to place her police department\nunder a general of marines may in\ncale that not the federal govern\nment, but some one in Pennsylvania,\nmay be responsible for such failure\nof prohibition, as Gov. Plnchot may\nhave observed at home, and which he\nhas mistakenly assumed as typical\nof the nation.\"\nGov. Plnchofs attack on federal en\nforcement was characterised by Mr.\nHaynes as \u201cso filled with Innuendo,\nsuggestions of Insincerity and lack\nof effectiveness, as well as serious\nconclusions, that, unanswered, it'\ncould but do great harm to prohi\nbition law enforcement.\"\nThe prohibition commissioner as\nserted the governor had been invited\nto discuss the enforcement question\nat headquarters here and had not ac\ncepted. and added that \"unfortunate\nly he has seen fit to discuss these\nmatters in public print and on the\nplatform.\u201d\nThe governor\u2019s chief complaint,\nsaid Mr. Haynes, seems to be \"the\ndepartment\u2019s Inability to give him\nand his state officers unlimited au\nthority to visit and Inspect the busi\nness of permittees at all hours, both\nday and night, when he knows, or\ncould easily find out, that the depart\nment has no such authority under\nthe law as to either prohibition offi\ncers or state officials. But this can\nnot In any way be interpreted to\nmean,\u201d the commissioner added, \u201cthat\nboth federal and state officers may\nnot go Into a brewery or distillery at\nany hour, day or night, provided It Is\nopen or In operation, or If entrance\ncan In any wise be obtained. And\nsuch Is the present practice as to\nprohibition agents.\u201d\nReferring to the statement by the\ngovernor that withdrawals of alcohol\nto be denatured have nearly trebled\nIn two years, Mr. Haynes said that,\ndue to business depression, the year\n1021 showed the smallest use of in\ndustrial alcohol in any year since\n1915, and that It was \"obviously\nabsurd\u201d to select the former year for\ncomparison.\nAs to Mr. Plnehot\u2019s statement that\n'\u2018lllegal withdrawals of whisky con\ntinue to Increase.\u201d Mr. Haynes said\n\"the best evidence that leakage has\nstopped from the bonded warehouses\nthrough fraudulent permits is the\nquality of liquor being used on the\nbootleg market today.\u201d\nBig Shoe l&lues\nPrices Cat far Quick Stock-Hcduciion\nspecifics nr m old-time price!\n;3\nI Wonderful $1.98\nValues at I\nMluti' Black ar Brown Lacr Boys\u2019 Brown or Black Lace Shoes.\nShoes. Rubber keel*. A Q English Uit, with A j AQ\nEnglish or broad toe. 4) ,VO rubber heels. Sises 4) f, VO\n1 1\nLittle Gents\u2019 er\nBrown Lace Shoes. Solid |A sfieil _\nheels*! d.| aa q O W ild \"\u2018f* th\" 1\n\u2022J 5\u00bb $1.98 'T rr.*. $1,98\nMen\u2019s Strictly All Solid L. <1\nLeather Work Shoes, pU\nable brown leather appera.\noar-pleee leather taper\nsoles, over-weight leather 4\ncounter soles; Scant Shoes\nIn all sises. AQ for Men and tp i AA\ni; .\u2019i y K, rr*. 51.98 a?ss:si*9B\nRUBBERS FOR ENURE FAMILY\nComplete Line of High-Quality Rubbers\nChildren's Rubbers 7Qc Ladies'Rubbers Q(W\u00bb Q AQc\nSizes to 11 Sizes 2j/< to 8 DaJ C Z, afO\nMisses* Heavy Rolled-edge Men\u2019s Storm Rubbers AQ C\nRubbers MXy* Sizes 6to 11......... %JQ\nSizes 11 Yz to 2\nn Men\u2019s Quality Storm\nI Boys* Rubbers QQc Rubbers $1 .39\nSizes 11 to 2. ZIO Sizes 6 to 11. 1\n$1.25 Men\u2019s Rolled-edge tl AQ\n1 Heavy-sole Rubbers i\nSizes 2*6 to o.\u2022\u00bb-\u00ab.\u00ab\nI i\nBranch Store 729 7th\n3100 M Street Cr%CQQg||9 N.W.\nREGIMEN